  <compounddef id="RADIXS" kind="page">
    <compoundname>RADIXS</compoundname>
    <title>RADIX$ Function</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">RADIX$(integer-expression,<sp/>integer-expression)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Converts an <bold>integer value</bold> (first parameter) into a <bold>string representation</bold> using the radix (base) specified by the second parameter. The radix must be between <computeroutput>2</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>36</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect1 id="RADIXS_1examples-107_1s1"><sect2 id="RADIXS_1examples-107_1s2"><sect3 id="RADIXS_1examples-107">
<title>Examples</title><para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>RADIX$(255,<sp/>16)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;FF&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>RADIX$(10,<sp/>2)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;1010&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">PRINT<sp/>RADIX$(12345,<sp/>36)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Produces <computeroutput>&quot;9IX&quot;</computeroutput>.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3></sect2></sect1>
<sect1 id="RADIXS_1notes-106_1s1"><sect2 id="RADIXS_1notes-106_1s2"><sect3 id="RADIXS_1notes-106">
<title>Notes</title><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Valid radix range is <computeroutput>2</computeroutput> (binary) through <computeroutput>36</computeroutput> (digits + A–Z).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Returned value is always uppercase.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Negative numbers are prefixed with <computeroutput>-</computeroutput>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Useful for formatting numbers in arbitrary bases beyond standard decimal, hexadecimal, or octal.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>To parse a string in an arbitrary base back into an integer, use <ref refid="RADIX" kindref="compound">RADIX</ref>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
